content:
The function returns when all the threads have completed their work, at which point it returns a vector of all the transformed words.

A word is converted by taking all its letters after the first letter (the head), moving them to the end, and adding "ay" to the end. For example:

    input_vec = ["california", "edabit", "rust"];

    output_vec = pig_latinify(input_vec);
    // => ["aliforniacay", "edabitay", "ustray"]

## Restrictions

Do not use the `join` function of Rust's `std::thread` module. Doing so will cause a test failure.
